<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880520-0159 </DOCNO><HL> Consumer Spending in Japan </HL><SO> </SO><CO> JAPAN </CO><DATELINE> TOKYO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Japanese consumer spending will continue to grow, adding fuel to the nation's economic expansion, the Economic Planning Agency found in a survey. The poll, of 5,025 families, showed that the seasonally adjusted index that measures consumers' purchasing plans rose 2.6% in 1988's first quarter from the prior three months, to its highest level since the agency began using the index in its present form in June 1982. </TEXT></DOC>